# Zilo, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Zilo () is a rural locality (a selo) in Botlikhsky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia. The population was 1,215 as of 2010. There are 8 streets.
Geography
Zilo is located 32&nbsp;km southeast of Botlikh (the district's administrative centre) by road, on the left bank of the Unsatlen River. Kizhani is the nearest rural locality.
